<br>
However, I do not think the death penalty is the best option.  I tend to agree with the Bill O' Reilly school of punishment.  <br>
<br>
These criminals should be doing hard labor out with 2 basic sets of clothes, no amenities, no magazines, no cigs, no alcohol, no nothing.  Army officers would run the camps.  It would do a lot more to reform criminals than our horrible jail system.  Also, criminals would be less likely to commit crimes since 20 years of HARD labor with no tv, no gym, no nothing, is far less appealing than prisons as they currently are.  I also suggest charging the criminals for the meals and everything else (small prices of course).  Thus criminals would know that in going to jail they are hurting their families monetarily.  When they got out they could easily work off the debt.  It would decrease crime 100 times over.<br>
<br>
Often times life in prison is only marginally worse (or possibly better) than life for some of these people in their current situations.  So what's the risk for them in robbing a bank or killing a person in a drug deal?  At the very worst they go to prison.<br>
<br>
Also, don't give me that 2nd amendment bullshit.  The second amendment was designed for the time it was written, the founding fathers weren't Miss Cleo.  No one *needs* guns right now other than the army, policemen, etc..  While I don't know if outlawing guns is best atm, I disagree that people have the *right* to bear arms.<br>
<br>
That liberal statistics about black males on death row or Bush's executions in correlation to conditions in Texas makes are bullshit, too.  People get this distorted information then they spread it around like gospel. 9 times out of 10 if you look beyond the statistics, they can easily be explained by other factors, which are sometimes not politically correct so they aren't mentioned, but they are there are same.   Drawing a blind correlation like that between social services and putting people to death in Texas is flat out ignorant.  The best guess I could give for low social services rankings in Texas would be that Texas has the largest numbers of illegal aliens present of any state in the US.  You don't think that drains social services?  Oh, nm, obviously putting serial rapists and murderers to death caused that problem too!<br>
