<br>
It's been a number of years since I last saw the exact figures, but back in the mid 90's this was accurate.<br>
<br>
Approximately 98.7% of all shootings occur within 7 feet.  *Not* '30 meters'.  Of the remaining shootings.. 85% occur within 15 feet. and 13% occur within 21 feet.<br>
<br>
There is a reason that police firing ranges have range lines at 7, 15, and 21 feet my friends.<br>
<br>
Range is a non-issue with guns vs. knives/bats - it has been proven over and over that if a knifeman charges you from 21 feet and you have a gun in a holster, the knifeman will get to you and stab you before you are able to get the gun into play.  This is why police have their guns drawn and ready to use against folks wielding weapons when those folks are fairly far from the police.<br>
<br>
Anyway, not weighing in on the main thread, just thought I'd give you some statistics about the actual distances involved in most shootings.<br>
